		on Wednesday April 10, 2024 @12:37PM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23286970&amp;cid=64383618">#64383618</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64383618"><p>The best solution I can think of to the problem of being surrounded by various compounds is to develop a paranoid schizophrenia towards all molecules. Plant tissue for example, contain thousands of various alkaloids with unpronounceable names only barely decipherable with an organic chemistry textbook. Most of which were specific developed by the plant to kill animals -- like humans. Who wants those inside them?  Sure, in "ingredients" they say "mango puree" or something. Do you know all the compounds and thousands of complex molecules in mango puree?  Our liver has to work overtime to detox all the toxic molecules that plants have developed to avoid being eaten and for pure revenge or maybe even in some twisted plant-pleasure way to try to kill us. Do you know what [FW]-[SGNH]-x-[GD]-{F}-[RKHPT]-{P}-C-[LIVMFAP]-[GAD] is? It's the consensus peptide sequence of the cytochrome P450 cysteine heme iron ligand -- programming that exists with the sole purpose of ensuring your body gets rid of molecules ASAP. Yes, we would be dead without it or if not dead fucked up. God evolved that. He fixed the fine structure constant such that it would enable cytochrome P450 to exist because he knew complex life can't persist without the ability to detox. I certainly wouldn't wish anyone live life without cytochrome P450 enzymes. Anyway, once you realize that everything has molecules, you realize the only way to live is in a pure, clean, elements-only state. The only way to live life is to avoid all the molecules being forced on us everyday. They are all bad. There is no molecule out there that won't kill a mouse if injected into a mouse in sufficient quantity. Think about that.</p></div>
	</div>

